President Barack Obama has proclaimed November 20, 2014, as National Child's Day in the United States. In his proclamation, he emphasizes the importance of providing opportunities for children to succeed and reach their full potential. The President highlights the significance of early education and pledges to expand access to preschool and high-quality early learning programs. He also mentions efforts to improve public schools and ensure every child has a healthy start in life through initiatives like Let's Move! and the Affordable Care Act. President Obama calls on citizens to observe National Child's Day and work together to support the dreams of all children.